 John McMillian, "Selling Spectrum Rights," <I>Journal of Economic Perspectives</I>, Vol. 8, No. 3 (Summer 1994), pp. 145-162.
<p>
Jora R. Minasian, "Property Rights in Radiation: An Alternative Approach to Radio Frequency Allocation," <I>The Journal of Law and Economics</I>, Vol. 18, No. 1 (April 1975), pp. 221-272.
<p>
Jora R. Minasian, "The Political Economy of Broadcasting in the 1920's," <I>The Journal of Law and Economics</I>, Vol. 12, No. 2 (October 1969), pp. 391-403.
<p>
Milton Mueller, "Reform of Spectrum Management: Lessons From New Zealand," Reason Foundation <I>Policy Insight</I> No. 135, November 1991.
<p>
Richard Nunno, "Advanced Television: Radiofrequency Spectrum Issues," Congressional Research Service <I>Report for Congress</I>, 96-74 SPR, January 18, 1996.
<p>
Richard Nunno, "FCC Auctions: Legislation in the 104th Congress," Congressional Research Service <I>Report for Congress</I>, 95-923 SPR, Updated October 25, 1995.
<p>
<I>The Telecom Revolution: An American Opportunity</I>, Progress and Freedom Foundation, May 1995.
<P>
<I>U.S. Spectrum Management Policy: Agenda for the Future</I>, National Telecommunications and Information Administration, U.S. Department of Commerce, February 1991.
<p>
<b>Endnotes:</b>
<p><ol>
<li>P.L. 104-104. For more information and detailed critiques of the original House and Senate bills, see Adam D. Thierer, "A Report Card on the Pressler Telecommunications Plan (S. 652)," Heritage Foundation <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/ib209.html"><I>Issue Bulletin</I> No. 209</a>, May 5, 1995; Adam D. Thierer, "Improving the House Telecommunications Plan (H.R. 1555)," Heritage Foundation <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/bgup255.html"><I>Backgrounder Update</I>  No. 255</a>, July 11, 1995; and Adam D. Thierer, "Telecommunications Unbound," <I>The World and I</I>, November 1995, pp. 66-71.<p>
