    <li>Thomas A. Brooks, "Stored Value Cards Raise Many Issues About FDIC Coverage," <I>Banking Policy Report,</I> March 4-16, 1996, p. 16.
  <li>See, for example, Randall S. Kroszner and Raghuram G. Rajan, "Organization Structure and Credibility: Evidence from Commercial Bank Securities Activities Before the Glass-Steagall Act," National Bureau of Economic Research <I>Working Paper</I> No. 5256, September 1995.
   <li>White, "Before the Glass-Steagall Act," pp. 40-42.
    <li>Benston, <I>The Separation of Commercial and Investment Banking,</I> p. 38.
    <li>Andrew S. Carron, <I>The Plight of the Thrift Institutions</I> (Washington, D.C.: The Brookings Institution, 1982), p. 30.
    <li><I>Ibid</I>., p. 12.
    <li>Alan Gart, <I>Regulation, Deregulation, Reregulation: The Future of the Banking, Insurance and Securities Industries</I> (New York: John Wiley and Sons, Inc., 1994), p. 25.
    <li>White, "Before the Glass-Steagall Act," p. 36.
    <li>Gerald P. O'Driscoll, "Insurance Agents Seek a Sweetheart Deal in Congress," <I>Knight-Ridder Financial News,</I> October 17, 1995.
    <li>Michael E. Porter, "Capital Disadvantage: America's Failing Capital Investment System," <I>Harvard Business Review,</I> September-October 1992, p. 67.
    <li>Michael T. Jacobs, "How U.S. Financial Regulations Reduce the Time Horizons for U.S. Investment," <I>Cato Review of Business & Government,</I> Vol. 15, No. 4 (October 1994) , pp. 62-63.
    <li>Nikhil Deogun, "Back to the Fray: Displaced by Mergers, Some Bankers Launch Their Own Start-ups," <I>The Wall Street Journal,</I> March 1, 1996, p. A1.
    <li>Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation.
    <li>Kroszner and Rajan, "Is the Glass-Steagall Act Justified?"  p. 829.
    <li>The possibility of risky investments can be mitigated further by removing the moral hazard created by federal deposit insurance. This issue will be discussed further in upcoming studies in this series.
    <li>For a complete comparison of firewall provisions as contained in the two bills, see Robert Eager <I>et al.</I>, "Memorandum: RE: Financial Modernization Legislation: Leach II, D'Amato/Baker and the Treasury Department Proposals," Gibson, Dunn & Crutcher, March 21, 1995.
    <li><I>Barnett Bank of Marion County, N.A. v. Nelson, Florida Insurance Commissioner, et al.</I>, No. 94-1837, decided March 26 1996, official decision not yet printed.
    <li>Michelle Singletary, "Borrowing by the Touch," <I>The Washington Post,</I> March 30, 1996, p. C1.</ol>
<p>
